#: src/workspace-trust.md:1
msgid "Workspace trust"
msgstr ""

#: src/workspace-trust.md:3
msgid ""
"Helix has a number of potentially dangerous features, namely LSP and ability "
"to use local to workspace configurations. Those features can lead to "
"unexpected code execution. To protect against code execution in dangerous "
"contexts, Helix has a workspace trust protection, which will prevent these "
"potentially dangerous features from running automatically."
msgstr ""

#: src/workspace-trust.md:5
msgid "Helix will not trust any workspace by default."
msgstr ""

#: src/workspace-trust.md:7
msgid ""
"By default, it will prompt about trust when you open new file in a workspace "
"where you didn't make a decision about trust yet."
msgstr ""

#: src/workspace-trust.md:9
msgid ""
"If you decide not to trust a workspace and don't want to be prompted about "
"trust every time you start a new session in it, you can exclude the "
"workspace by choosing `Never` option in trust selection window."
msgstr ""

#: src/workspace-trust.md:11
msgid ""
"You can always make current workspace trusted by running `:workspace-trust` "
"command, and untrust it with `:workspace-untrust`."
msgstr ""

#: src/workspace-trust.md:13
msgid ""
"Lists of trusted and excluded workspaces, delimited by newline characters, "
"are stored in `~/.local/share/helix/trusted_workspaces` and `~/.local/share/"
"helix/excluded_workspaces` correspondingly."
msgstr ""

#: src/workspace-trust.md:16
msgid "Configuration"
msgstr ""

